3 SECTION 11. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
4 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 809.1 of Title 17, unless there
5 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
6 The Legislature finds that the prudent development of solar
7 energy resources requires assurances that the rights of private
8 landowners should be protected, that such landowners have access to
9 adequate information to verify the accuracy of their payments, among
10 other protections, and that public and mineral interest operators
11 receive sufficient notice of planned developments.
12 SECTION 12. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
13 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 809.2 of Title 17, unless there
14 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
15 As used in the Oklahoma Solar Energy Development Act:
16 1. "Commencement of construction" means the date on which the
17 owner or developer of a solar energy facility installs a post or
18 posts into the ground for panel or inverter foundations. The term
19 shall not include environmental assessments, surveys, preliminary
20 engineering, site preparation, or other activities associated with
21 assessment of development of the solar resources on a given parcel
22 of property;
23 2. "Facility" means a solar energy facility;
24
Req. No. 17207 Page 21

1 3. "Owner" means the entity having a majority equity interest
2 in a solar energy facility, including its respective successors and
3 assigns;
4 4. "Racking system" means the permanent structural framework,
5 including foundations, piles, mounts, or tracking equipment that is
6 designed to support, anchor, and orient photovoltaic modules or
7 related solar-energy-producing equipment at a solar energy facility
8 and that is integral to the facility's ability to generate
9 electricity;
10 5. "Solar energy facility" means an electric-generating
11 facility using photovoltaic or solar-thermal technologies with a
12 nameplate capacity greater than one (1) megawatt alternating current
13 (AC), designed to deliver energy to the electric grid and not
14 primarily to on-site load, unless otherwise specified by state law;
15 and
16 6. "Working interest" means the interest in a well or the
17 interest in a unit created by order of the Corporation Commission
18 that entitles the oil and gas lessee, or the lessee’s successor or
19 assign, to drill for and produce oil and gas.
20 SECTION 13. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
21 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 809.3 of Title 17, unless there
22 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
23 For landowners who are paid based on the amount of electrical
24 energy produced from the conversion of solar energy, the owner of
Req. No. 17207 Page 22

1 any solar energy facility shall provide a statement within ten (10)
2 business days of the payment to the landowner in consideration for
3 the use of the property of the landowner to generate electrical
4 energy. The statement shall provide, at a minimum, information
5 reasonably necessary to assist the landowner an understanding of the
6 basis for the payment to the landowner and a means of confirming its
7 accuracy.
8 SECTION 14. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
9 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 809.4 of Title 17, unless there
10 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
11 A. Any landowner who has, through a lease, easement, or other
12 arrangement, allowed a solar energy facility foundation or racking
13 system to be placed on the property of the landowner and who is paid
14 based on the amount of electrical energy produced from the
15 conversion of solar energy shall have the right to inspect the
16 records of the owner of the solar energy facility for the purpose of
17 confirming the accuracy of any payments made to the landowner within
18 the past twenty-four (24) months.
19 B. The owner of any solar energy facility, any portion of which
20 is located in this state, upon request of a landowner with the right
21 to inspect records as set forth in subsection A of this section,
22 shall make available, within a reasonable time, all records,
23 documents, data, and other information, or copies thereof, as are
24 necessary for a landowner to conduct the inspection specified in
Req. No. 17207 Page 23

1 subs ection A of this section. The records shall be made available
2 within the confines of this state and in a location and manner that
3 affords a landowner reasonable access to the records during normal
4 business hours. The landowner shall be permitted one request per
5 calendar year and be afforded a reasonable length of time to
6 complete the inspection but shall not cause undue disruption to the
7 operations of the owner during the inspection. The records shall be
8 subject to the confidentiality requirements contained in the
9 respective landowner lease agreement.
10 SECTION 15. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
11 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 809.5 of Title 17, unless there
12 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
13 A. The owner of any solar energy facility shall report to the
14 Oklahoma Corporation Commission the electrical energy generated by
15 the solar energy facility, the nameplate capacity of the solar
16 energy facility, and the location of the solar energy facility.
17 B. If a solar energy facility contains generating units with
18 different nameplate capacities, the information required in
19 subsection A of this section shall be reported separately for each
20 nameplate capacity.
21 C. The information required by this section shall be reported
22 on an annual basis, with the information due not later than March 1
23 of each calendar year.
24
Req. No. 17207 Page 24

1 SECTION 16. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
2 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 809.6 of Title 17, unless there
3 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
4 A. Prior to commencing construction of a solar energy facility,
5 the owner of the solar energy facility shall obtain and keep in
6 effect either:
7 1. A commercial general liability insurance policy with
8 coverage limits consistent with prevailing industry standards; or
9 2. A combination of self-insurance and excess liability
10 insurance.
11 B. The owner shall cause the owner of the land on which the
12 solar energy facility is located to be named as an additional
13 insured under the policy.
14 C. The owner shall deliver to the landowner a certificate of
15 insurance evidencing the policy. The landowner shall be given not
16 less than thirty (30) days prior written notice of any material
17 modification, cancellation, or termination of the insurance policy.
18 SECTION 17. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
19 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 809.7 of Title 17, unless there
20 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
21 A. The owner of a solar energy facility shall submit a
22 notification of intent to build a facility to the Oklahoma
23 Corporation Commission at least six (6) months before the
24 commencement of construction, as defined in Section 12 of this act.
Req. No. 17207 Page 25

1 The Corporation Commission shall prescribe the form and submittal
2 requirements of the notification; provided, the information required
3 on the notification form shall include a description of the
4 facility, the nameplate capacity, the general location of the
5 facility, and a map of the project boundary.
6 The owner of the solar energy facility shall send copies of the
7 notification to the board of county commissioners of every county in
8 which all or a portion of the solar energy facility is to be located
9 within twenty-four (24) hours of filing said notification with the
10 Corporation Commission. If all or a portion of the solar energy
11 facility is to be located within the incorporated area of a
12 municipality, a copy of the notification shall also be sent to the
13 governing body of the municipality within twenty-four (24) hours of
14 filing said notification with the Corporation Commission.
15 B. Within six (6) months of submitting the notification to the
16 Corporation Commission as provided for in subsection A of this
17 section, the owner of the solar energy facility shall cause a copy
18 of the notification to be published in a newspaper of general
19 circulation in the county or counties in which all or a portion of
20 the solar energy facility is to be located. Proof of publication
21 shall be submitted to the Corporation Commission.
22 C. Within six (6) months of submitting the notification to the
23 Corporation Commission as provided in subsection A of this section,
24
Req. No. 17207 Page 26

1 the owner of the solar energy facility shall cause a copy of the
2 notification to be sent, by certified mail, to:
3 1. Any operator, as reflected in the records of the Corporation
4 Commission, conducting oil and gas operations upon all or any part
5 of the surface estate on which the solar energy developer intends to
6 construct the solar energy facility;
7 2. Any operator, as reflected in the records of the Corporation
8 Commission, of an unspaced unit or a unit created by order of the
9 Corporation Commission, conducting oil and gas operations for a unit
10 where all or any part of the unit area is within the geographical
11 boundaries of the surface estate on which the solar energy developer
12 intends to construct the solar energy facility;
13 3. All lessees of oil and gas leases covering the mineral
14 estate underlying any part of the tracts of land that are filed of
15 record with the county clerk in the county where the tracts are
16 located and whose primary term has not expired. This paragraph
17 shall apply to tracts of land not described in paragraphs 1 and 2 of
18 this subsection on which the solar energy developer intends to
19 construct a solar energy facility;
20 4. Any owner of a working interest arising from an oil and gas
21 lease, as reflected in the records of the Corporation Commission, of
22 a unit created by order of the Corporation Commission, where all or
23 any part of the unit area is within the geographical boundaries of
24
Req. No. 17207 Page 27

1 the surface estate on which the solar energy developer intends to
2 construct the solar energy facility; and
3 5. Any operator of a well permitted by the Corporation
4 Commission for injection or disposal purposes, as reflected in the
5 records of the Corporation Commission, where such well is located
6 within the geographical boundaries of the surface estate on which
7 the solar energy developer intends to construct the solar energy
8 facility.
9 If the solar energy developer makes a search with reasonable
10 diligence and the whereabouts of a party entitled to notice cannot
11 be ascertained or the notice cannot be delivered, an affidavit
12 attesting to such diligent search shall be submitted to the
13 Corporation Commission.
14 D. Within sixty (60) days of publication of the notification in
15 a newspaper of general circulation as provided for in subsection B
16 of this section, the owner of the solar energy facility shall hold a
17 public meeting. Notice of the public meeting shall be published in
18 a newspaper of general circulation and submitted to the board of
19 county commissioners in the county or counties in which all or a
20 portion of the solar energy facility is to be located. The notice
21 shall contain the place, date, and time of the public meeting.
22 Proof of publication of the notice shall be submitted to the
23 Corporation Commission. The public meeting shall be held in the
24
Req. No. 17207 Page 28

1 coun ty or in one of the counties in which all or a portion of the
2 solar energy facility is to be located.
3 E. With regard to the surface estate upon which the owner of a
4 solar energy facility intends to construct the facility, at least
5 sixty (60) days before entering upon the surface estate for the
6 purpose of commencement of construction, the owner shall provide
7 written notice, by certified mail, of its intent to construct the
8 solar energy facility to the parties described in subsection C of
9 this section.
10 The notice shall contain a map or plat of the proposed location,
11 with sufficient specificity to identify the solar energy facility to
12 be located on the governmental section and the approximate date
13 construction is proposed to commence. If the solar energy developer
14 makes a search with reasonable diligence and the whereabouts of a
15 party entitled to notice cannot be ascertained or the notice cannot
16 be delivered, an affidavit attesting to such diligent search shall
17 be submitted to the Corporation Commission. Within thirty (30) days
18 of receiving such notice, any party described in subsection C of
19 this section shall reciprocate, in writing by certified mail, the
20 relevant site, operational, and infrastructure information
21 sufficient to assist with the safe construction and operation of the
22 solar energy facility. This information shall include American Land
23 Title Association surveys, if available, and technical
24 specifications for existing subsurface or surface improvements.
Req. No. 17207 Page 29

1 Any information provided by an oil and gas operator or solar
2 energy developer pursuant to this subsection shall be confidential
3 and proprietary. The parties shall:
4 1. Use such information solely for the purposes of this
5 section;
6 2. Not disclose such information to any third party without the
7 prior written consent of the disclosing party, except as required by
8 law or order of a court of competent jurisdiction or the Corporation
9 Commission; and
10 3. Upon written request of the disclosing party, return or
11 destroy all such information and certify the same in writing.
12 The confidentiality obligations of this subsection shall not be
13 limited by or contingent upon the terms of any landowner lease
14 agreement or surface use agreement. Violation of this provision
15 shall constitute grounds for the Corporation Commission to suspend
16 or revoke a permit issued under this act, in addition to any other
17 remedies available at law or in equity.
18 F. The owner of a solar energy facility shall not commence
