12 SECTION 18. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
13 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 809.8 of Title 17, unless there
14 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
15 A. When applicable, a solar energy developer shall submit site
16 plans and fees for any new solar energy facility to the Office of
17 the Oklahoma State Fire Marshal for review. Such site plans shall
18 be submitted when the solar energy facility is sixty percent (60%)
19 complete in design development. The site plans shall include an
20 accurate representation of:
21 1. Photovoltaic modules;
22 2. Inverters;
23 3. Monitoring and control equipment;
24 4. Substations;
Req. No. 17207 Page 31

1 5. Collection lines;
2 6. Access roads;
3 7. Temporary construction areas;
4 8. Operation and maintenance facilities; and
5 9. Other relevant supporting infrastructure.
6 B. Review by the Office of the Oklahoma State Fire Marshal
7 shall be limited to compliance with applicable fire and building
8 safety codes, including:
9 1. The Oklahoma-adopted International Building Code, as
10 codified at OAC 748:20-2-1; and
11 2. The 2018 Edition of the International Fire Code, as codified
12 at OAC 748:20-4-1.
13 C. The Office of the Oklahoma State Fire Marshal or local
14 authority having jurisdiction, where applicable, shall complete any
15 review subject to this section as soon as practicable, but in no
16 event later than thirty (30) calendar days following receipt of
17 complete site plans and fees. In the event the Office of the
18 Oklahoma State Fire Marshal or local authority having jurisdiction
19 does not complete its review within thirty (30) calendar days, any
20 applicable permits and certificates shall be deemed issued.
21 D. During the pendency of the review by the Office of the
22 Oklahoma State Fire Marshal, the following on-site activities may
23 proceed:
24 1. Timbering, clearing, and grubbing vegetation;
Req. No. 17207 Page 32

1 2. Civil grading and earthwork;
2 3. Installation of stormwater pollution prevention measures and
3 best management practices;
4 4. Installation of laydown areas and substation concrete
5 foundation pads, including rough grading and gravel;
6 5. Installation of racking systems, inverters, photovoltaic
7 modules, low-voltage collection systems, and above-ground
8 transmission poles;
9 6. Public road improvements, entrance installations, and
10 service road construction;
11 7. Placement of construction trailers with temporary power,
12 fiber connections, and portable sanitation facilities;
13 8. Sub-grade open trenching;
14 9. Installation of on-grade concrete foundations; and
15 10. Installation of structural columns and beams.
16 E. The Office of the Oklahoma State Fire Marshal may assess a
17 plan review fee at a rate of six cents ($0.06) per square foot of
18 actual erected solar facilities, provided that the total fee shall
19 not exceed Five Hundred Thousand Dollars ($500,000.00) for any
20 single solar energy facility. The amount of such fee shall have a
21 reasonable connection to the work actually performed by the Office
22 of the Oklahoma State Fire Marshal.
23 F. Of the fees collected pursuant to this section:
24
Req. No. 17207 Page 33

1 1. Seventy-five percent (75%) shall be distributed to the local
2 fire department providing primary fire protection services to the
3 jurisdiction where the facility is located, within sixty (60) days
4 of receipt. Funds distributed pursuant to this paragraph shall be
5 used solely for fire protection, fire prevention, inspections,
6 training, or emergency response activities related to the facility;
7 and
8 2. Twenty-five percent (25%) shall be distributed to the permit
9 issuing authority, whether the Office of the Oklahoma State Fire
10 Marshal or a recognized local authority having jurisdiction, if
11 delegated.
12 G. If the Office of the Oklahoma State Fire Marshal delegates
13 any site plan review, permitting, or similar authority over a solar
14 energy facility to a recognized local authority having jurisdiction,
15 fees and timing shall continue to conform the requirements of this
16 section.
17 H. The provisions of this section shall only apply to solar
18 energy facilities designed to provide electricity to the grid, as
19 well as any utility-scale solar energy facility designed to deliver
20 electricity directly from a generating facility to a single end-use
21 customer.
22 SECTION 19. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
23 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 809.9 of Title 17, unless there
24 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
Req. No. 17207 Page 34

1 A. In addition to complying with the provisions of this act, the
2 owner of a solar energy facility shall comply with the provisions of
3 the Commercial Solar Facility Decommissioning Act in accordance with
4 Section 820 et seq. of Title 17 of the Oklahoma Statutes.
5 B. An owner shall submit evidence of financial assurance
6 sufficient to secure the performance of its decommissioning
7 obligations in accordance with the Commercial Solar Facility
8 Decommissioning Act on or before the tenth year of operation of the
9 facility and thereafter upon request by the Commission, but at least
10 once every five (5) years for the life of the solar energy facility.
11 The amount of such financial assurance shall be calculated in
12 accordance with the Commercial Solar Facility Decommissioning Act,
13 but shall not be less than one hundred twenty-five percent (125%) of
14 the estimate of the total cost of decommissioning, less the salvage
15 value of facility equipment and any portion of the value of such
16 equipment pledged to secure outstanding debt.
17 SECTION 20. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
18 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 809.10 of Title 17, unless there
19 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
20 The Oklahoma Corporation Commission shall have authority to
21 promulgate rules as necessary to implement the provisions of the
22 Oklahoma Solar Energy Development Act and to set fees necessary to
23 perform the duties and responsibilities of the Commission pursuant
24 to the act. The Oklahoma Corporation Commission shall have
Req. No. 17207 Page 35

1 excl usive jurisdiction to enforce the provisions of this act that
2 are within its authority.
3 SECTION 21. This act shall become effective July 1, 2026.
4 SECTION 22. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
5 of the public peace, health or safety, an emergency is hereby
6 declared to exist, by reason whereof this act shall take effect and
7 be in full force from and after its passage and approval.
